@flexiarg coordination/cross-validation-protocol
@title Cross Validation Protocol (G1)
@keywords cross-validation, review, check, replay
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/coordination-protocol futon-theory/rapid-debugging]
@theory-grounding [A3(Evidence-driven) A1(Auditability)]

! conclusion:
  If you want robustness against self-serving validation, define a cross-validation path where another agent (or a deterministic harness) can re-run the validation on the same evidence.

  + context: Validation should be replayable by someone other than the executor.
  + IF:
    you want to reduce confabulation and improve trust in PUR outcomes

  + HOWEVER:
    a single agent validating its own work can silently lower standards

  + THEN:
    require validation evidence to be sufficient for replay, and define a cross-validation protocol that can be invoked from the PUR chain

  + BECAUSE:
    coordination quality depends on independent verification of claimed progress

